Pour the cold @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @Orange{1/2}. Trim the @Green Beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds.

Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm chunks. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Place the @Diced Chicken Thigh{260%g} into a #bowl{} with the @Cornflour{20%g} and @salt{pinch}. Mix together until well coated.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a generous drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the diced chicken and season with @pepper{}. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, transfer to a bowl and pop the (now empty) pan back on medium-high heat.

Add the green beans and pepper to the pan. Cook until softened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #measuring jug{}, combine the @Honey{15%ml}, @Ginger Puree{15%g}, @Tomato Ketchup{1} and @Plain Flour{1/2%tbsp} until thoroughly mixed and no clumps of flour remain.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Whisk the @Soy Sauce{25%ml}, @Rice Vinegar{15%ml} and @Water for the Sauce{50%ml} into the jug until smooth, then set aside.

Once the veg has softened, stir the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in the sauce mixture and bring to the boil, stirring, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the cooked chicken back into the pan. Stir to glaze in the sauce, then remove from the heat.

Squeeze in the orange juice and add the orange zest. Stir until combined, then taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the orange chicken, spooning over all the sauce from the pan. Enjoy!